FBIS4-51971 "dreas087_c_94020" FBIS-EAS-94-087 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA North Korea SRV Communist Party Delegation Leaves 28 Apr SRV Communist Party Delegation Leaves 28 Apr SK3004144894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 28 Apr 94 SK3004144894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 28 Apr 94 Korean BFN [Text] The Vietnamese Communist Party delegation led by Hong Ha, secretary of the Vietnamese Communist Party Central Committee, left for home on a train on 28 April. Hwang Chang-yop, secretary of the Workers Party of Korea Central Committee; Kim Yang-kon, vice director of a department of the party Central Committee; and Duong Chinh Thuc, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK, bid farewell to the delegation at Pyongyang Station.
